    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{6t}{t^{2}+4t+3}-\frac{3t}{t+1}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{3t}{t+3}, t\ne -1</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{6t}{t^{2}+4t+3}-\frac{3t}{t+1}} 
      \amp = {\frac{6t}{\left(t+1\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+3\right)}-\frac{3t}{t+1}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{6t}{\left(t+1\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+3\right)}-\frac{3t}{t+1}} \cdot \frac{(t+3)}{(t+3)} \\
      \amp = {\frac{6t}{\left(t+1\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+3\right)}-\frac{3t\mathopen{}\left(t+3\right)}{\left(t+1\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+3\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{6t-3t\mathopen{}\left(t+3\right)}{\left(t+1\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+3\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{6t-3t^{2}-9t}{\left(t+1\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+3\right)}} \\
      \amp = {\frac{-3t^{2}-3t}{\left(t+1\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+3\right)}} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-3t\mathopen{}\left(t+1\right)}}{{\left(t+1\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+3\right)}} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{3t}{t+3}, t\ne -1}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>t+1</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>t \ne {-1}</m>.</p>
</solution>
